		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName> <date>Nov 16 1850</date></p>
			<p>Editor of the Occident</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">Dear Sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(4)">In your<lb/> esteemed Paper of <date>Nov.</date> in an article<lb/> entitled &#8220;Letters on Christianity&#44; No 4. By<lb/> a Jewish layman&#8221; Pg 308. The following<lb/> remark &#8220;Not because I fear the effects<lb/> of their writings <hi rend="underline">but because the columns of</hi><lb/><hi rend="underline"> their religious papers are closed to us</hi>&#8221;<lb/> I wish to say to the &#8220;<hi rend="underline">Layman</hi>&#8221; that I was <lb/> not before aware of this fact. The &#8220;Jewish<lb/> Layman&#8221; is deeply interested in Judaism<lb/> and would sustain it&#44; and no doubt<lb/> would extend its principles over the world</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">He thinks that fair discussion would<lb/> turn the scale in favor of Judaism<lb/> If I am wrong in my <sic>christian</sic> faith<lb/> I am a lost man. If Judaism is<lb/> the true way of salvation&#44; upon pain<lb/> of Endless Perdition I am bound to listen<lb/> to its teachings&#44; and open my mind<lb/> to conviction of its truths&#44; and when con<lb/>vinced to embrace it at all worldly har<add>&#63;</add>s</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Hence if the &#8220;Jewish Laymen&#8221; is disposed he<lb/> is welcome to occupy two or three pages of<lb/> the &#8220;Jewish Chronicle&#8221; with sound&#8212;kind&#8212;and</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>fair discussion every month for the benefit<lb/> of between 2000 &#38; 3000 <sic>christian</sic> readers<lb/> of both ministers and Layman. Provided<lb/> he can be answered through your columns<lb/> in articles of Equal length&#44; <sic>cander</sic>&#44; kindness<lb/> &#38; fairness. I mean not this for a challenge<lb/> but in order that the comparative merits<lb/> of Judaism and Christianity may be fairly<lb/> placed before the Jewish and Christian com&#45;<lb/>munities with the highest esteem for<lb/> the people of <placeName>Israel</placeName> and desire &#38; do them<lb/> Eternal good. I remain</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">Your humble servant</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">E B McGreger</persName> Editor of</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">Jewish Chronicle</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Office Corner of Spruce &#38; Nassau St</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(4)"><placeName>New York</placeName></p>
          
